; to shake aggro i usually get it back in short order...<br>
<br>
Slasra,  Suprisingly  it's  not  the wizzys on raids such as  a Hot raid that i loose aggro to.. Now granted the last time i raided HOT was back in August at which time i lead continuous hot raids each day for 7 straight days, of which the shortest hot raid lastest 8 hours the longest was 22+ hours. In short i was  recruiting and leading  &quot;pickup&quot; raids to get my hot armor to better serve the guild that i was in at that time, because the guild as a whole wasn't really interested in doing HoT 2-3 times a week.  No item was ever defaulted my rules were quite simple.. Win  1 item then your out till either all in your armor type win an item or else no one in that armor type needed it.  Hell we even  had to designate  guild represenitives to roll on items that no  one on the raid needed a few times.. I was the  MA, the organizer and for the most part the one managing the raid the entire duration each nite. Now the times i lost aggro, predominatly it was to a pally or SK, whom was either using a sweet 2-hander and/or stunning/doting,lifetapping.. Only occasionally did a mage or wizzy draw aggro, most likely from sitting after a couple quick nukes to close together..  ( only a guess on my part as i was having to endure the  &quot;NO clue what mouthwash is Mob_01&quot;).<br>
   Now one might contend, since the raid's were  &quot;pickup&quot; then<br>
skillz or the lack thereof was the problem....  I would beg to disagree, in that regard, as i would wager it was more of  &quot; i gotta get EXP every kill mentality&quot;  that generally occurs in any raid  regardless of whether it's a pickup raid or (insert guilds name) raid.... So if anyone is to be blamed then i would have to shoulder the brunt of the  blame..  Simply because, I was a raidleader for my guild and i never once lead,planned or proposed any raid that would have given myself or our other MA capable warriors in the guild better weapons... Thats my fault,  i joined the guild to Help them become better in terms of raid  skillz and  equipment.  I've always earned my own gear on my own dice luck... Because to me  i am no better then any other person on the raid.....  So what if i was often the &quot;MA&quot;.  Doesn't mean the other wars were less capable or less deserving of upgrades, but in the end my desire to help everyone else first  clouded my judgement in some aspects as to how i was actually helping the guild. Better weapons and armor would have made the then  current  MA capable warriors even more effiecient at that assigned task and perhaps would have reduced failed or wiped raids and made us more mana effiecient as a whole... <br>
  In the end i deguilded in frustration at my percieved class failure of fullfilling a warriors intended purpose, which may  or may not have lead to other people leaving the guild rather then continue trying to improve the guild as a whole.. Either way, done is done  and in the end, whether exp group or raid environment..   The group or raid can be only as good as the  player who's supposed to be  Holding aggro.. <br>
