  But let me ask everyone  what a Warriors role is &quot;typically&quot;?<br>
<br>
  If you said , hold mob aggro.. then examine what items a player with this goal in  mind is going to be wanting....<br>
<br>
  Hp items,stamina buff items, and AC, well AC  at least till they hit  1200 unbuffed ac being  as this appears to be the soft cap atm... Then it's resist items since the  changes to resists was made and more  HP items.  While  monks,rogues,pallys,SK's  in general don't &quot;have&quot; to focus on  Hps or AC so much.  but  perhaps it is  also depends on what your  &quot;perception&quot; is of what  a warriors role on a raid is...<br>
   Now then lets look at haste.... most warriors tend to go with haste items on the belt slot  because of the higher ac found on most back slot items... Again perhaps this is just perceptions  but being as both the monk and rogue  epic has 40 percent haste attached to them.. that broadens the damage ouput margin quite abit untill the war gets to  Ntov, VP  or compariable zone where 40 percent haste items with great ac drops.. Now then of all the guilds on Quell, perhaps 6 maybe 7 have or are currently doing  Ntov or tougher. Granted at least 1 warrior in each of the these guilds has nice items in each slot. But overall i would wager the vast majority of warriors focus on  Hps and AC then stamina and Resists before worrying about  attack buffing or anything other then tauting generating weapons and untill their guild goes to Ntov or higher or else they change guilds or  get invited on these raids then in general  available gear  chosen follows  hp/ac 1st and foremost.<br>
<br>
 Oh, and on  the posts on  the warrior board...  i would suggest  you read it again....<br>
Furor  was   supposedly  Tanking the mob  and  the other warrior was in the back  doing his impersonation of a rogue..<br>
So what we need now to really get a better picture of the situation.. is  Precisely  what weapons, what buffs and what effect  items were being used by each player listed on  Furor's post, without that info,  verifiying, or disputing his statement is somewhat ridiculous  unless  your in a guild that has compariable gear as  Furors magelo indicates he has.... In which  case, you  could do your own log parses and see how your guilds warriors compare DPS wise against the other melee.<br>
